<TITLE> War crimes suspect arrested in Magura </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Magura, May 6 (bdnews24.com)Police arrested on Wednesday an alleged Pakistani collaborator during independence war after charges were pressed against him. Mostofa Mollah, , 58, hailed from village Kalupara in Sadar Upazila. Sharafat Ali, son of martyred freedom fighter Belayet Ali Master, had filed the case with the district chief judicial magistrate's court. The case is in brief that Mollah killed the complainant's father on Oct. 27, 1971. Sagir Miah, officer in charge of Sadar Police Station, said they had arrested Mostofa at his house after the chief judicial magistrate ordered them to take legal steps. Police petitioned the court to remand him for seven days to questioning, he said. 
